Description.LocalizedString: Centuries old and still stylish.
Formerly an elegant evening ensemble, The Doctor has customized it to his needs, weaving high-tension wires through the fabric.
An abundance of bloody malpractices are stabbed, twisted, and cut into his body. He wanted to feel what his last patient did before he opened them up.
If you’re going to expand your mind—and someone’s ribcage—you have to be willing to get dirty.
Reinforced with leather, this coat can be subjected to any ill treatment in the lab without leaving a trace. Ideal for project undisclosed to the public.
His sharp claws ripped through his gloved hands and tore his clean suit.
The muscles and nerves of multiple corpses were forced together, creating a monstrosity that thrived on the pain of existence.
He learned a lot about exotic types of pain over the years. Bug eggs under the skin was one of the worst.
He could inflict a powerful shock.
He could inflict a devastating electric punch.
His kimono featured exquisite fabric and intricate handmade details.

Description.LocalizedString: The uniform makes it official. You have command over the lives of others, and the authority to destroy them.

Description.LocalizedString: Electricity surges across the mask's terminals, ridding the mind of unwanted thoughts.
A mask that prevents infection from the love bug.
There’s no laughing gas coming through the mask and yet he can’t help but smile. It might have to do with the dangerous amount of electrodes he's streamed into his limbic cortex.
The Doctor’s experiments started with simple questions. For example, what if someone was sleep deprived, eyes pried open, and injected with steady streams of adrenaline? The results were fascinating.
He designed a brass helmet that made test subjects run, turn, and stop via remote control.
A sinister, scarred face that featured a twisted grin.
What The Doctor lacked in looks, he more than made up for in intelligence.
It didn’t take long for the reproducing creatures to get completely out of control.
He stalked victims endlessly.
He ambushed victims endlessly.
A horrifying face between sharp fangs.

Description.LocalizedString: There's nothing more invigorating than being jolted back to life after a spell in the deep abyss.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A soiled instrument to apply pain of a terrible kind.
A silvery spiked stick crowned with a crimson ruby, which is set in the mouth of a hungry beast thirsting for blood. An elegant way to administer your lethal dose.

Description.LocalizedString: A gentleman’s cane for a gentleman’s murder.
Healing energies crackle along this staff, ready to purge you of all kinds of impurities, sinful thoughts, and life.

The arm of a surgical robotic tool. Though it once effectively drilled into human skulls, The Doctor tore it from its pedestal—possibly out of jealousy. That’ll teach it to take away jobs from humans.
One of the Doctor’s first torture devices, made before the CIA money came flooding in. Holds a sentimental place in his heart.
High bandwidth tube with electrical pulses that can inflict and transmit a high amount of pain per second.
A jolting and adjustable wrench for all of purposes, mainly shocking attacks.
A shock stick covered in flesh. Electric impulses course through the nerves.
The moth is a cautionary tale: sometimes the things you are most attracted to end up destroying you.
The fastest way to a sugar rush.
He had a lot of affection for this weapon, able to disrupt his patient's voluntary control of muscles without killing them.
He had a lot of affection for this weapon, able to stun his patient during a chase.
A precise weapon for a sharp electric shock.
A military weapon from ancient times once believed to be charged with electricity.
A prototype device specially made to electrocute captured enemy sailors. The navy forbid its production, though flattered The Doctor by calling it "cruel and grotesque."
He ended upon a strange realm surrounded by the ruins of ancient pyramids.
His victims quaked in terror, their screams echoing through his hollow chest.
He raised the scepter over his fallen subject, a triumph of his reign of terror.
